I added butter and syrup, didn't help. Smells like the plastic cup it's cooked in, but I think the cup would probably taste better. Sorry, I just can't get behind these. Microwave pancakes do exist, not sure why this is even a thing. zero stars from me.

I spent some time in Japan this summer and got to love Royal Milk Tea (canned version.) The cans are too expensive to get in the States, so I thought I'd try this powder. The packets were much larger than I was expecting, and there is a lot of powder in one packet (see photo.) After reading the reviews I used two packets in my cup. It was delicious and just as I remembered drinking in Japan! Very pleased with this Royal Milk Tea product. The instructions are in traditional Chinese, according to my translation program. You just add hot water, stir, and drink. I didn't feel a need to add any milk or sugar/honey, it was perfect the way it is. I haven't tried to make it cold yet, but I'm sure I will soon! Definitely would buy again. Great price, fast delivery.
